57 (f) If an individual transformational youth is already on parole on the effective date of
58 this Act, and has lived less than 3 years on parole on the effective date of this Act, the time that
59 said transformational youth has lived on parole on the effective date of this Act shall be counted
60 as constituting time lived on parole for purposes of termination of parole. The Board shall issue
61 a Certificate of Termination of sentence to said transformational youth pursuant to Section 130A
62 of chapter 127, and notify all parties and individuals of the Certificate of Termination of
63 sentence, after the transformational youth has lived for 3 years on parole, in accordance with
64 subsection (d).
